name: CQ Events
description: Events from commit queue. This was closely modeled after the JSON data that is sent to chromium-cq-status.appspot.com. All tags and certain fields, however, were excluded: owner, message, state, timestamp. Fields that have been renamed have noted this in their description.

fields.name: timestamp_millis
fields.description: Time of event, in milliseconds since the UNIX epoch.

fields.name: action
fields.description: Type of CQ event, e.g. PATCH_COMMITTED.

fields.name: attempt_start_usec
fields.description: Timestamp when the CQ attempt was started (user clicked on CQ bit).

fields.name: cq_name
fields.description: Name of the CQ that sends this event.

fields.name: issue
fields.description: Issue ID that is processed by CQ; at most 100 characters.

fields.name: patchset
fields.description: Patchset ID that is processed by CQ; at most 100 characters.

fields.name: dry_run
fields.description: True if CQ is in dry-run mode.
